- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper presents a new algorithm for computing all pairs shortest paths in a distributed setting.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the algorithmic approach and analysis for computing shortest paths.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the algorithm uses only the directed edges in the graph for communication.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with graph theory and shortest paths.
- cs.AL (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the time complexity of the algorithm.
